==English==

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈkəʊʃ@(r)/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"k@US@(r)/

===Etymology===
[[Yiddish]] ''kosher'', from Hebrew

===Noun===
'''kosher'''

# the [[Jew]]ish [[religion|religious]] practice that specifies which [[food]] is fit to [[eat]] and how it is to be [[prepare]]d.

====Translations====

*Finnish: [[kosher]]
*Hebrew: [[כשר]]

===Adjective===
'''kosher'''

# (of food) prepared in accordance with Jewish religious practices.
# (generally) in accordance with standards or usual practices, 
:i.e ''"Is what I have done '''kosher''' with Mr Smith?"''  

